-- Saudi's Alhokair plans debut sukuk, picks Samba as arranger
-- By David French
-- Tue May 27, 2014 02:58AM EDT
-- None



DUBAI, May 27 (Reuters) - Fawaz Abdulaziz Alhokair Co <4240.SE>, the Saudi Arabian retailer which franchises brands such as Zara and Marks and Spencer in the kingdom, plans to issue its debut riyal-denominated sukuk, it said in a bourse filing on Tuesday.

Alhokair will begin meeting fixed income investors on Tuesday and has chosen the investment banking arm of Samba Financial Group <1090.SE> to arrange the deal, the filing added. No value or tenor of the planned sukuk was given in the statement.